<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AUTOMATIC POSITIVE LOCKING TRACTION DIFFERENTIALS
        (NOSPIN/DETROIT LOCKER) - DISASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mark the differential case halves so they can be reassembled in their original position when
                repair or inspection is completed (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400302">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400302" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400302" filename="../figg14/g1400302.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Mark Differential Case Halves</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert the NoSPIN differential retaining bolt and washer assembly. Thread the nut
                fingertight against the washer (
                <hotlnk document="s14003_9.xml" xrefid="f1400301">Figure 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>If a retaining bolt and washer assembly are not available, hold the differential case firmly
                        as the last bolts are being removed from the case halves to absorb spring pressure and prevent
                        possible injury.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Separate the case halves and remove the NoSPIN differential assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400303">Figure 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400303" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400303" filename="../figg14/g1400303.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Separate Case Halves</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Release the retaining bolt and washer assembly while firmly holding the NoSPIN differential
                to absorb the spring pressure.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove side gears, springs, spring retainers, driven clutch assemblies and spider (or
                central driver) assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
